description: The plane was approaching the airport in Bishkek, the capital, when it struck a cluster of houses.
title: Turkish Cargo Plane Crashes Into Village in Kyrgyzstan, Killing Dozens
title_page: Turkish Cargo Plane Crashes Into Village in Kyrgyzstan, Killing Dozens - The New York Times
text:
The Kyrgyz Emergencies Ministry said that at least 12 people had been taken to the hospital.
An image on the website of the television station owned by Kyrgyzstanâ€™s government showed a large section of the nose of the aircraft, including the cockpit windows, on the ground after the plane apparently crashed through a building. Wreckage was strewed across a wide area.
A video of the crash scene showed emergency workers in a snow-covered neighborhood, with pieces of the plane interspersed among houses and wreckage in flames. Tents were set up to help shelter displaced residents from temperatures of about 13 degrees Fahrenheit (minus 11 Celsius).
